<subsection xml:id="subsec-wedge-product">
<title>Wedge Product</title>
<paragraphs xml:id="para-wedge-definition">
<title>Definition</title>
<p>The wedge product between two vectors <m>\mathbf{a},\mathbf{b}\in \mathcal{V}_n</m> where <m>\mathcal{V_n} \sube \mathbb{R}^n </m> is given by:</p>
<me>\mathbf{a}\wedge\mathbf{b} = |a| |b| \underbrace{\mathbf{e_\mu}\mathbf{e_\nu}}_{=\mathbf{i}} \sin{\theta}</me>
<p>where <m>\mathbf{e_\mu}\perp\mathbf{e_\nu} \Rightarrow \mathbf{i}^2=-1</m>.</p>
<note>
<p>The wedge product is the antisymmetric component of the geometric product.</p>
</note>
</paragraphs>
